abstract: "SQL-SI (SQL Structural Intelligence) proposes a new paradigm that extends SQL from a relational query system into a structural intelligence backend. The approach introduces persistent structural objects (such as trajectories, graphs, and Common Concept Core (CCC) patterns), metric-space reasoning, and policy-aware decision layers (PDS) on top of traditional SQL systems.\n\nIn current AI pipelines, structured intelligence layers are often bypassed, with models operating directly on tokens or embeddings. SQL-SI restores this missing layer by enabling reusable, verifiable, and metric-comparable structural representations derived from SQL data.\n\nThis repository provides a conceptual framework, figure system, and minimal runnable Java prototype demonstrating trajectory extraction, CCC discovery, structural object storage, and comparative analysis against traditional SQL recomputation.\n\nSQL-SI is positioned as a proposal and reference scaffold rather than a complete database system, aiming to bridge database systems and next-generation structural intelligence architectures such as DBM-SI."

